0317c215-bdd7-4232-a2d3-252a07c4e50e.do_description: To make the output, you have to...duplicate the entire grid, then fill in the solid color to exactly match the checker pattern. Finally result should be entirely checker patterned.
0317c215-bdd7-4232-a2d3-252a07c4e50e.grid_description: The output grid size...the same as the input grid size.
0317c215-bdd7-4232-a2d3-252a07c4e50e.see_description: In the input, you should see...a checker patterned square surrounded on two sides by a solid color.

0d534d3b-44a1-4d65-8865-21a503aacb4a.do_description: To make the output, you have to...imagine the same pattern on the input grid 6x6 as output grid
0d534d3b-44a1-4d65-8865-21a503aacb4a.grid_description: The output grid size...the same size as a input grid
0d534d3b-44a1-4d65-8865-21a503aacb4a.see_description: In the input, you should see...the pattern on a black grid

11bb3fbb-629a-4376-8d4e-aac2b53aad3f.do_description: To make the output, you have to...copy over the input. Continue the alternating pattern of colors so they replace the color that is behind them. You should end up with only the alternating color pattern as the same size grid as the input.
11bb3fbb-629a-4376-8d4e-aac2b53aad3f.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same.
11bb3fbb-629a-4376-8d4e-aac2b53aad3f.see_description: In the input, you should see...an alternating pattern of colors on top of another color.

2fffe9b5-a550-43ba-83ec-afd7eada133d.do_description: To make the output, you have to...reverse the two colors of the pattern. (Example: blue, red, blue, red)Remove the border in the input picture, so that the entire grid with the new pattern.
2fffe9b5-a550-43ba-83ec-afd7eada133d.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same as the input.
2fffe9b5-a550-43ba-83ec-afd7eada133d.see_description: In the input, you should see...a pattern of alternating colors, with a border on the right

30aaf17d-7d68-4249-8b23-a4e4ddc91c3a.do_description: To make the output, you have to...most of block will fill by pink and orange color
30aaf17d-7d68-4249-8b23-a4e4ddc91c3a.grid_description: The output grid size...in last row of block will replaced by pink and green
30aaf17d-7d68-4249-8b23-a4e4ddc91c3a.see_description: In the input, you should see...first grid mixed of color of block will show,in second grid size of block and colour will change, in thrid block will reduce of size

32f16546-705c-4c9c-9700-4eed02bff76b.do_description: To make the output, you have to...do a pattern of 2 different colored squares, like pink then green, pink then green, all through the grid, but on 3 of them add a 2 side border of a solid color, you choose how many border rows you want to add
32f16546-705c-4c9c-9700-4eed02bff76b.see_description: In the input, you should see....colored squares on a grid, every other one is a different color, three are surrounded on 2 sides with solid colored rows, number of rows is up to you

50bb27f6-d62f-42e9-96d0-d25b33db8ce9.do_description: To make the output, you have to... Replace the border with the same checkerboard pattern until the entire grid is covered. It should just be a checkerboard and nothing else.
50bb27f6-d62f-42e9-96d0-d25b33db8ce9.grid_description: The output grid size... remains the same.
50bb27f6-d62f-42e9-96d0-d25b33db8ce9.see_description: In the input, you should see... a checkerboard pattern with a different color bordering it.

5632dfa8-d38e-4d9b-84ac-60a36f146929.do_description: To make the output, you have to...continue the checkerboard pattern in the corner to fill out rest of grid
5632dfa8-d38e-4d9b-84ac-60a36f146929.grid_description: The output grid size...same as input
5632dfa8-d38e-4d9b-84ac-60a36f146929.see_description: In the input, you should see...a checkerboard pattern in one corner

5a0c0aa2-56d9-4dc7-807d-a72d01317dbd.do_description: To make the output, you have to...copy the two color square onto the new grid. Fill the background squares with the alternating color pattern so the entire grid is two colors.
5a0c0aa2-56d9-4dc7-807d-a72d01317dbd.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same size as the original.
5a0c0aa2-56d9-4dc7-807d-a72d01317dbd.see_description: In the input, you should see...a square with alternating colors with some background pixels in a different color surrounding it on two sides.

84ae155c-ec4a-4034-b671-c743fb4f5a6f.do_description: To make the output, you have to...recreate the checkerboard pattern but with the colors switched
84ae155c-ec4a-4034-b671-c743fb4f5a6f.grid_description: The output grid size...focus on the checkerboard pattern
84ae155c-ec4a-4034-b671-c743fb4f5a6f.see_description: In the input, you should see...a checkerboard pattern bordered by a solid color

91a2cf4a-de7f-43e6-98a1-13a270aebb79.do_description: To make the output, you have to...repeat the diagonal pattern throughout the entire grid.
91a2cf4a-de7f-43e6-98a1-13a270aebb79.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input grid size.
91a2cf4a-de7f-43e6-98a1-13a270aebb79.see_description: In the input, you should see...a diagonal pattern in the top left portion of the grid followed by solid colored lines to the right and bottom.

9f524d2d-d044-4f77-bd8e-6c95e7b32334.do_description: To make the output, you have to...replace the third color by continuing the pattern created by the first two colors. By the time you are done, you should have an entire grid of two alternating colors.
9f524d2d-d044-4f77-bd8e-6c95e7b32334.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same.
9f524d2d-d044-4f77-bd8e-6c95e7b32334.see_description: In the input, you should see...three different colors, two of those colors are in an alternating pattern that forms a square or rectangle. The third color surrounds the shape made by the first two colors.

a4fcf962-8bc4-42c8-b382-d8654d6fb63f.do_description: To make the output, you have to...apply the pattern to the new grid while not using the single color item that includes the bottom and right in the input grid. You will only use the pattern in the input grid and apply it to the new output grid.
a4fcf962-8bc4-42c8-b382-d8654d6fb63f.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same as the input grid
a4fcf962-8bc4-42c8-b382-d8654d6fb63f.see_description: In the input, you should see...a square pattern with a single color to its right.

b7df4e30-fc74-42d9-bf38-bdc735c341f2.do_description: To make the output, you have to...me choose corner place of blue colors
b7df4e30-fc74-42d9-bf38-bdc735c341f2.grid_description: The output grid size...not changed grid size.
b7df4e30-fc74-42d9-bf38-bdc735c341f2.see_description: In the input, you should see...the black key on the ouput

e8a82612-caec-4c8c-aa9b-b8236ce248f9.do_description: To make the output, you have to...remove the solid color border and repeat the corner pattern
e8a82612-caec-4c8c-aa9b-b8236ce248f9.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same
e8a82612-caec-4c8c-aa9b-b8236ce248f9.see_description: In the input, you should see... a pattern in the top left corner and a border of a different color

ee430603-0318-4542-9b8f-0982d14841d2.do_description: To make the output, you have to...remove the solid colored border, and just continue the two color pattern to fill the whole grid.
ee430603-0318-4542-9b8f-0982d14841d2.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input grid size.
ee430603-0318-4542-9b8f-0982d14841d2.see_description: In the input, you should see...a repeating pattern of two colors. You will also see a solid colored border on the bottom and right sides.
